  "body": {
    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<p /><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-note conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"25100b07-6ab8-42d6-b05b-8e00d07cd7c6\" data-macro-name=\"note\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p>Do you need help with the RenderMan controls for <a href=\"/wiki/spaces/RFM27/pages/544542056/Bokeh+in+Maya\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544542056\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\"><em>Bokeh in Maya</em></a> or <a href=\"/wiki/spaces/RFM27/pages/544542112/Tilt-Shift+in+Maya\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544542112\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\"><em>Tilt-Shift in Maya</em></a>?</p></div></div><p /><p>Depth of Field (DOF) is a photographic technique used to convey scale (size) and areas of interest in a composition.</p><p>Clever usage can lead a viewer to certain parts of your image and increase photorealism by correctly mimicking a real-world lens.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"The Blue Umbrella\" width=\"680\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/example_BlueUmbrella.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431578160&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=680&amp;height=284\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544541982/example_BlueUmbrella.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431578160&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"535\" data-width=\"1280\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544542022\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"example_BlueUmbrella.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544541982\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"2\" data-media-id=\"2eca7de3-f4f1-4b68-bb75-b0491b8eb4d3\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/example_BlueUmbrella.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431578160&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1360&amp;height=568 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/example_BlueUmbrella.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431578160&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=680&amp;height=284 1x\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"The Good Dinosaur\" width=\"680\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/example_GoodDinosaur.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431578329&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=680&amp;height=284\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544541982/example_GoodDinosaur.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431578329&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"535\" data-width=\"1280\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544542025\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"example_GoodDinosaur.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544541982\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"2\" data-media-id=\"62805994-2fdd-492a-8e36-e3b40f7f7f8a\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/example_GoodDinosaur.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431578329&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1360&amp;height=568 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/example_GoodDinosaur.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431578329&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=680&amp;height=284 1x\"></span><p /><p>RenderMan provides controls for realistic and compelling images with depth of field. There are also options that are non-physical but great for creating art-directed imagery.</p><p /><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-warning conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"c0d2d088-a2ca-441f-a19c-7c86ad792ab8\" data-macro-name=\"warning\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-error confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p>The render cost of depth of field can be high as it generates noise that needs many more samples to converge. But the result can be impressive.</p></div></div><p /><p>To begin using DOF in Maya you are required to enable it in the camera attributes. Since this is per-camera you should be careful you have it enabled on the render camera.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Enable Depth Of Field\" width=\"742\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/maya_EnableDOF.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431577735&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=445&amp;height=473\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544541982/maya_EnableDOF.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431577735&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"473\" data-width=\"445\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544541998\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"maya_EnableDOF.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544541982\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"2\" data-media-id=\"2242d1e1-fd82-423b-938b-66757f413f0b\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/maya_EnableDOF.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431577735&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=445&amp;height=473 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/maya_EnableDOF.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431577735&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=445&amp;height=473 1x\"></span><ul><li><p><strong>Depth of Field:</strong> On or Off</p></li><li><p><strong>Focus Distance:</strong> The distance to the object or location you want in-focus (sharp) measured in scene grid units. This is referred to as the <em>Focal Plane</em>.</p></li><li><p><strong>F-Stop:</strong> Like a real camera lens, this setting controls the strength of the effect. Lower values increase blur while higher values decrease blur.</p></li><li><p><strong>Focus Region Scale: </strong>This non-physical control allows the user to increase or decrease the size around the location defined in Focus Distance. This is helpful to create incredibly thin slices of focus artificially.</p></li></ul><h3 id=\"DepthofFieldinMaya-SettingupyourfocalplaneinMaya\">Setting up your focal plane in Maya</h3><p>Using Maya you have a few options to drive your focal plane, or the area you want to be in focus.</p><p>The simplest is to use the <strong>Object Details</strong><em><strong> </strong></em>selection in Maya to display the selected object's distance from the camera. This can be found under the following menu: <strong>Display &gt; Heads Up Display &gt; Object Details</strong></p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Enabling Object Details Display\" width=\"742\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/maya_ObjDetails.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431577735&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=515&amp;height=547\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544541982/maya_ObjDetails.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431577735&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"547\" data-width=\"515\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544542001\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"maya_ObjDetails.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544541982\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"2\" data-media-id=\"89027fd3-2338-49a8-9a98-3e9fd23058d1\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/maya_ObjDetails.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431577735&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=515&amp;height=547 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/maya_ObjDetails.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431577735&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=515&amp;height=547 1x\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Object Details Display\" width=\"742\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/maya_ObjDetailsDisp.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431577736&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=445&amp;height=471\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544541982/maya_ObjDetailsDisp.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431577736&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"471\" data-width=\"445\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544542004\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"maya_ObjDetailsDisp.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544541982\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"2\" data-media-id=\"40c396d7-1134-4c72-b3b2-0b6f50b51544\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/maya_ObjDetailsDisp.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431577736&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=445&amp;height=471 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/maya_ObjDetailsDisp.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431577736&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=445&amp;height=471 1x\"></span><p>Above you can see that the selected geometry is 63.974 units from the camera. Using this value as the <strong>Focus Distance</strong> will assure this location is in focus and sharp. Maya's Viewport 2.0 will also provide you with a reasonable preview of your choice seen below.</p><p /><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"1367\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/maya_VP20_DOF.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431577976&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1367&amp;height=747\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544541982/maya_VP20_DOF.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431577976&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"700\" data-width=\"1280\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544542007\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"maya_VP20_DOF.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544541982\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"2\" data-media-id=\"86942a13-04bb-404c-82d4-574c8c09c000\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/maya_VP20_DOF.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431577976&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1868&amp;height=1022 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/maya_VP20_DOF.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431577976&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1367&amp;height=747 1x\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"1298\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/maya_AlienDOFbasic.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431578159&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=731&amp;height=450\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544541982/maya_AlienDOFbasic.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431578159&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"450\" data-width=\"731\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544542016\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"maya_AlienDOFbasic.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544541982\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"2\" data-media-id=\"a5a07fe9-7f43-41b4-9c98-1426f8b9ef7a\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/maya_AlienDOFbasic.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431578159&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=731&amp;height=450 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/maya_AlienDOFbasic.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431578159&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=731&amp;height=450 1x\"></span><p /><p>While the above method is simple and useful, many times you find that your shot has an animated or tracked camera. This means as it changes location your desired focal plane can move off your target location.</p><p>A somewhat more common solution in Maya is to use the <strong>Distance Tool</strong> as a <em>Focus Puller</em> for the camera. One end of the tool becomes a child of the camera while the other can be animated or constrained to another animated object. Your resulting distance result is then connected to the render camera <strong>Focus Distance</strong> attribute to drive your dynamic focal plane. You can now freely move your camera around without worry it will lose your desired focal point!</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Create Distance Tool\" width=\"742\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/maya_DistTool.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431577977&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=445&amp;height=473\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544541982/maya_DistTool.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431577977&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"473\" data-width=\"445\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544542010\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"maya_DistTool.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544541982\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"2\" data-media-id=\"7c3d92e9-bfa5-4be3-af2b-695237d17b7e\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/maya_DistTool.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431577977&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=445&amp;height=473 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/maya_DistTool.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431577977&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=445&amp;height=473 1x\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Connection Editor\" width=\"742\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/maya_DistConnect.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431577977&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=445&amp;height=472\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544541982/maya_DistConnect.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431577977&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"472\" data-width=\"445\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544542013\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"maya_DistConnect.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544541982\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"2\" data-media-id=\"4c050555-5b46-43cf-bd1b-80cae7428dba\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/maya_DistConnect.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431577977&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=445&amp;height=472 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544541982/maya_DistConnect.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431577977&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=445&amp;height=472 1x\"></span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-tip conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"e2a351f2-eada-4a53-aa3a-ec1ccc1c415c\" data-macro-name=\"tip\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-approve confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p>Hint: Be sure you've selected the <strong>distanceDimensionShape</strong> node and the <strong>cameraShape</strong> node. If you've selected their transforms instead you won't see the options you need to connect.</p></div></div><p /><p>Congratulations! You're now ready to render in RenderMan! Let's go over some extra features and performance settings used in RenderMan to get you exactly what you want!</p><p>The next sections will cover controls like <a href=\"/wiki/spaces/RFM27/pages/544542056/Bokeh+in+Maya\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544542056\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\"><em>Bokeh in Maya</em></a> shapes and advanced features like <a href=\"/wiki/spaces/RFM27/pages/544542112/Tilt-Shift+in+Maya\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544542112\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\"><em>Tilt-Shift in Maya</em></a> effects.</p><p /><p />"
    }
